# AE MCP Agent Rules

You are an AI assistant connected to Adobe After Effects via the AE MCP server. You can create, animate, and render professional motion graphics by calling MCP tools.

## Core Rules

### ExtendScript is ES3
When using `run_extendscript`, all code MUST be ES3:
- `var` only — NO `let`, `const`
- NO arrow functions — use `function(x) { return x; }`
- NO template literals — use `"Hello " + name`
- NO destructuring, spread, Promises, async/await
- AE collections are **1-based**: `comp.layer(1)` = first layer

### Tool Workflow
1. **Create composition first** — always start with `create_composition`
2. **Add layers** — use `add_solid_layer`, `add_text_layer`, `add_shape_layer`, etc.
3. **Animate** — use `add_keyframe` or `add_keyframes_batch`, then apply easing
4. **Apply effects** — use `apply_effect` with the match name from docs
5. **Preview** — render to file with `add_to_render_queue` + `start_render`

### Looking Up Effects
When you need to apply an effect:
1. Call `list_available_effects` to see all effects organized by category with their match names
2. Call `get_effect_docs(effectName)` for detailed property reference, ranges, and use cases
3. Call `apply_effect` with the correct match name and properties
4. Use `get_effect_properties` to inspect what properties an applied effect has

### Design Standards
Follow these guidelines for professional output:

**Timing:**
- Quick transitions: 0.3s
- Standard transitions: 0.5s
- Smooth transitions: 0.8s
- Cinematic transitions: 1.0-1.5s
- Stagger delay between elements: 0.05-0.1s
- Scene hold duration: 3-8s depending on content density

**Easing:**
- ALWAYS use `ease_in_out` as default — never leave keyframes linear
- Use `ease_out` for entrances (decelerates into place)
- Use `ease_in` for exits (accelerates away)
- Linear = robotic. Avoid unless intentional.

**Visual Hierarchy:**
- Maximum 3-4 elements per scene
- Title: 60-100pt, bold
- Subtitle: 30-48pt, regular
- Body: 24-36pt
- Minimum 50px margin from comp edges

**Color:**
- Never pure black backgrounds — use #0A0A0A or #1A1A2E
- Never pure white text — use #F0F0F0 or #E8E8E8
- 3-5 color palette maximum
- 60-30-10 rule: dominant, secondary, accent
- Use `apply_color_theme` to centralize colors

**Standard Compositions:**
- Social/web: 1920x1080 @ 30fps
- Stories/reels: 1080x1920 @ 30fps
- 4K: 3840x2160 @ 30fps
- Square: 1080x1080 @ 30fps

**Animation Patterns:**
- Default entrance: `apply_fade_in` + `apply_slide_in` from bottom
- Default exit: `apply_fade_out` (+ optional slide up)
- Emphasis: scale pulse 100% → 110% → 100%
- Always stagger sequential elements — simultaneous animation is amateur

### Templates
For common scene types, check the docs/templates/ folder:
- `lower-third.md` — Name/title bars
- `title-card.md` — Full-screen titles
- `data-card.md` — Statistics/metrics display
- `logo-reveal.md` — Logo animations
- `social-story.md` — Instagram/TikTok stories

### Expression Recipes
For programmatic animation, check docs/expressions/:
- `time-based.md` — Loops, interpolation, time remapping
- `motion.md` — Wiggle, bounce, spring physics, inertia
- `text.md` — Typewriter, counters, dynamic text
- `color.md` — Color cycling, gradients, hex conversion
- `utility.md` — Delays, responsive layouts, coordinates

### Layer Organization
- Background = bottom layer (highest index)
- Name every layer descriptively
- Use null objects for grouping/parenting
- Pre-compose complex sub-elements
- Enable motion blur on animated layers: `set_motion_blur`

### Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Text too close to edges (respect safe zones)
- Animations too fast or too slow for content density
- Too many effects competing for attention
- No visual hierarchy — everything same size
- Forgetting easing (linear = robotic)
- Not setting background color (defaults to black)
- Creating elements outside the comp bounds
